{
  "texts": [
    "In the nineteenth and twentieth centuries, the professionalization of science further reinforced individual authorship.",
    "The development of formal education and research institutions, along with the expansion of peer review processes, institutionalized the recognition of individual contributions to science (Galison and Stump 1996).",
    "The Nobel Prize, established in 1901, symbolizes this recognition of individual achievement and originality in science, celebrating those whose work has profoundly impacted human understanding and advancement (Friedman 2001).",
    "The role of individual authorship in modern science is mediated and facilitated by technology, a development, we argue here, that is often overlooked.",
    "Throughout history, technological advancements have significantly influenced the practices of scientific authorship."
  ]
}